cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.NI 

This paper discusses security concerns in cloud computing and proposes a method to improve security using Moving Target Defense (MTD). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the dynamic reconfiguration of virtualized environments, which falls under the category of cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper discusses the evaluation of availability and security levels, which can be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of varying workloads and attack intensities, which can be categorized under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
